## **Phase 1 — Pre-deploy (per repo)**

1. **Commit work branch first** — follow [git_commit_push_release_deploy.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/git_commit_push_release_deploy.mdc) Phases 0–4.
2. **Record SHAs:**

```powershell
cd F:\project_workspace\<repo>
git fetch origin
git rev-parse --short HEAD                    # local work
git rev-parse --short origin/<deploy-branch>  # remote deploy (before)
```

3. **Sync release to work** (when deploy branch ≠ work branch):

```powershell
git checkout <deploy-branch>
git pull origin <deploy-branch>
git reset --hard <work-branch>
```

4. **When work branch = deploy branch** (event-site-manager, batch-jobs on release): push deploy branch only after commit.

---

## **Phase 2 — Push (triggers Amplify / ECS)**

```powershell
$env:GH_TOKEN = [Environment]::GetEnvironmentVariable('GH_TOKEN', 'User')
$env:GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY = 'true'

# Work branch (if different from deploy)
git push origin <work-branch>

# Deploy branch
git push origin <deploy-branch>
```

**Batch example (all six repos):**

```powershell
powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File `
  "F:\project_workspace\application-deployments\documentation\aws-infrastructure\_private\scripts\Invoke-ReleaseDeployAll.ps1"
```

(Ensure `GH_TOKEN` is set in the parent shell or script loads it from User env.)

